02:57.182 --> 03:01.697
I... started smoking crack when I was 12.

03:01.729 --> 03:04.764
That was when my uncle
started making me, like...

03:04.799 --> 03:07.600
Do stuff to him or whatever.

03:07.635 --> 03:09.869
Being high made me forget.

03:09.878 --> 03:13.747
When I'm high, everything
just sort of disappears.

03:13.782 --> 03:15.749
My stupid parents didn't believe me

03:15.784 --> 03:17.417
when I told them what happened.

03:17.453 --> 03:20.754
They just got pissed and called me a liar

03:20.789 --> 03:24.024
and kicked me out on the streets.

03:24.059 --> 03:25.359
It's just so hard to stay clean

03:25.394 --> 03:28.362
when I've been addicted
to this stuff for so long.

03:28.397 --> 03:32.416
But I've been clean now for 30 days.

03:32.931 --> 03:35.969
Ain't nobody here made
it without pain, so...

03:36.004 --> 03:38.783
Oh, god.

03:40.946 --> 03:42.786
All right, Roger. Call
me if you need anything.

03:42.807 --> 03:45.781
- Hey. How was it?
- I'm doing what I'm supposed to.

03:45.806 --> 03:48.115
- I want to see Carter.
- I got you a lawyer.

03:48.150 --> 03:49.449
I want to see Carter.

03:49.485 --> 03:51.451
- He can't change the laws, Aubry.
- Then get another lawyer!

03:51.487 --> 03:52.686
I am going to those meetings.

03:52.721 --> 03:53.987
I am sitting through that garbage every day

03:54.022 --> 03:56.656
I'm doing everything I
can. I promise you, I am.

03:56.692 --> 03:58.492
Your mom and Brian are flying in.

03:58.527 --> 03:59.993
I put them off long enough.

04:00.028 --> 04:02.996
Now, we need to get you some
new clothes, fix your hair.

04:03.031 --> 04:04.498
Carter loves me the way I am.

04:04.533 --> 04:07.834
Carter is in jail. Your family's here.

04:07.870 --> 04:10.170
You need to show that
you're making an effort.

04:17.379 --> 04:19.346
Damn it.

04:22.175 --> 04:23.474
So, what are we doing today?

04:23.509 --> 04:25.142
We're fixing this.

04:25.178 --> 04:27.077
Well, tell me what you don't like about it.

04:27.113 --> 04:28.312
Where do I start?

04:28.347 --> 04:31.624
I told the woman I want the
same haircut I walked in with,

04:31.649 --> 04:32.591
only shorter.

04:32.627 --> 04:34.226
Instead, she gave me this. Okay.

04:34.262 --> 04:35.527
Well, we can thin it out.

04:35.563 --> 04:37.196
And then she curled it.

04:37.231 --> 04:38.297
Well, we won't do that. Mm.

04:38.332 --> 04:40.966
We'll give you something easy to deal with.

04:41.002 --> 04:43.068
But before we get you shampooed,

04:43.104 --> 04:45.474
is it okay if I give you
a little head massage?

04:46.483 --> 04:48.366
What do you mean? What is that?

04:48.397 --> 04:50.163
Well, I put my hands on your head,

04:50.199 --> 04:54.835
and I massage a little bit,
just to get everything relaxed.

04:56.037 --> 04:57.571
I guess.

05:04.446 --> 05:08.482
So, are you new to Modesto?

05:10.422 --> 05:12.989
Yeah. Uh, yes.

05:25.452 --> 05:27.386
Mark!

05:27.421 --> 05:28.887
Oh, my god!

05:28.922 --> 05:31.790
Oh, my god! Hey.

05:34.828 --> 05:36.295
He's suing me.

05:36.329 --> 05:38.729
- He sent some man after me in a parking lot.
- He did what?

05:38.766 --> 05:40.866
Not suing... I don't know the word,

05:40.901 --> 05:43.802
but he's served papers.

05:43.836 --> 05:45.676
This is all about Matt's funeral?

05:46.423 --> 05:48.948
That man has no judgment

05:48.973 --> 05:51.607
he can't make a single decision on his own.

05:51.632 --> 05:53.298
And when he does, it's the wrong one.

05:53.333 --> 05:56.101
And Tom and Eve, they're completely...

05:56.136 --> 05:58.887
They turn everything into
an "us vs. them" situation.

05:58.912 --> 06:01.292
And you know Russ, always the follower,

06:01.317 --> 06:03.990
which leaves me as the
only one to fight for Matt

06:04.015 --> 06:05.281
they convinced Russ

06:05.316 --> 06:08.050
that Matt should be buried
in Oakland, of all places.

06:08.086 --> 06:10.153
Your brother deserves better than this.

06:10.188 --> 06:13.723
He was always there for
us when we needed him.

06:13.759 --> 06:16.626
Even his country, signing up after 9/11...

06:16.661 --> 06:18.561
That's the kind of person he was.

06:18.597 --> 06:20.663
Is there any chance he could win?

06:24.773 --> 06:28.141
I'll talk to Russ.

06:28.507 --> 06:30.540
Thank you.

06:31.737 --> 06:34.144
You have no idea.

06:36.386 --> 06:38.920
You look different. Get a haircut?

06:38.955 --> 06:41.356
Oh.

06:41.391 --> 06:44.292
It looks good, mom.

06:44.328 --> 06:46.227
It makes you look young.

06:53.337 --> 06:55.503
Are you sure you don't want to come in?

06:55.539 --> 06:57.572
No.

06:57.607 --> 06:59.607
Mom, it's the right thing to do.

06:59.643 --> 07:01.124
And I've done it.

07:01.149 --> 07:02.870
If you want to go in and pay your respects,

07:02.875 --> 07:04.341
I'll wait for you here.

07:04.376 --> 07:08.151
Okay.

07:26.734 --> 07:30.226
Go ahead, Mark. She'd like it.

07:32.730 --> 07:37.433
Doctors say she's improving,
responding to stimuli.

07:37.468 --> 07:41.937
Sometimes it's like she
squeezes back, you know?

07:41.973 --> 07:45.917
I can feel her trying.

07:45.942 --> 07:48.176
Can she hear us?

07:48.211 --> 07:51.446
I brought in a radio to play music to her.

07:51.481 --> 07:54.051
I talk to her.

07:54.076 --> 07:56.317
Don't I, sweetie?

07:56.353 --> 07:58.887
I pray with her.

08:00.957 --> 08:03.691
I'm so sorry.

08:03.727 --> 08:06.461
They're gonna take her off the ventilator.

08:06.496 --> 08:09.397
If she can breathe on her own,

08:09.432 --> 08:11.533
it's a sign she's gonna make it.

08:16.940 --> 08:19.908
Aren't you, girl? You're gonna make it.

08:21.878 --> 08:24.512
How you doing this morning, Mr. Nix?

08:24.548 --> 08:27.348
Can I call you "Carter"?

08:27.384 --> 08:29.150
He's your lawyer?

08:29.186 --> 08:32.153
Brother Timothy is here to represent you.

08:33.097 --> 08:35.222
Man, what you got... bad news or worse?

08:35.246 --> 08:38.169
It's very positive. The
lab results came back.

08:38.210 --> 08:40.844
The bullet recovered
from Matt Skokie's body

08:40.878 --> 08:42.510
doesn't match the ballistics

08:42.547 --> 08:44.346
from the gun found in your possession.

08:44.382 --> 08:46.015
The prosecution's known this,

08:46.050 --> 08:48.350
and they've kept it quiet
as long as they could.

08:48.386 --> 08:52.521
Their case is getting weaker.
They don't have the gun.

08:52.557 --> 08:55.024
They don't have your
DNA on the woman's body.

08:57.094 --> 08:59.114
So... what's it mean?

08:59.139 --> 09:01.582
Brother Timothy's trying
to get a bail hearing.

09:01.607 --> 09:04.200
- I'm not waiting.
- And based on the new circumstances,

09:04.235 --> 09:05.534
- we think we can get you bail.
- I'm gonna look these people in the eye

09:05.570 --> 09:07.043
and ask them why they're lying.

09:07.068 --> 09:10.139
So if I have a bail
hearing, can Aubry be there?

09:13.050 --> 09:14.577
Can she?

09:15.995 --> 09:17.413
It's open court.

09:17.448 --> 09:19.222
Anyone in the public can go,

09:19.247 --> 09:22.051
which means the families of the victims

09:22.086 --> 09:24.553
are going to be there, too.

09:24.589 --> 09:27.056
To parade their sad faces
and make you look like

09:27.091 --> 09:29.391
the very definition of
the fearsome black man.

09:29.427 --> 09:31.393
What's that got to do with Aubry?

09:31.429 --> 09:33.395
How will it look to have
the little white girl

09:33.431 --> 09:34.911
who turns your tricks waiting for you?

09:34.932 --> 09:37.066
- She's not a whore!
- She's a drug addict.

09:37.101 --> 09:39.902
You need to present yourself
with pride and dignity.

09:39.937 --> 09:42.071
In my red jumpsuit?

09:42.106 --> 09:43.973
With my hands and feet shackled?

09:45.009 --> 09:47.309
Clean yourself up.

09:47.345 --> 09:50.879
At least shave that mess on your face.

10:01.907 --> 10:03.907
Get it off.

10:03.942 --> 10:05.508
We called a painter.

10:05.545 --> 10:07.945
He can redo the wall, but
he can't get here until...

10:07.981 --> 10:11.649
Just get some paint. I'll do it myself.

10:33.973 --> 10:36.674
♪ I'm staring into this glass ♪

10:36.709 --> 10:40.211
♪ looking at my reflection ♪

10:40.246 --> 10:43.781
♪ thinking 'bout all we had ♪

10:43.816 --> 10:46.217
♪ 'bout your little laugh ♪

10:46.252 --> 10:50.421
♪ this whiskey's taking over ♪

10:50.456 --> 10:53.591
♪ so much I want to do over ♪

10:53.626 --> 10:56.160
♪ sitting all alone ♪

10:56.195 --> 11:01.699
♪ now in this empty home ♪

11:01.734 --> 11:06.583
♪ and you are gone ♪

11:06.608 --> 11:09.142
♪ I can't eat, can't sleep ♪

11:09.170 --> 11:13.072
♪ I miss my one and only ♪

11:14.008 --> 11:16.876
♪ so, please ♪

11:16.911 --> 11:20.413
♪ come back home ♪

11:23.551 --> 11:26.118
I mean, half of this is
just like nonsense, you know?

11:26.154 --> 11:27.720
They make you do work,

11:27.755 --> 11:30.156
make you go in, listen
to some dude sing songs.

11:30.191 --> 11:32.625
That dude was tired.

11:32.660 --> 11:34.460
But the rest of it's all good.

11:34.495 --> 11:37.396
Got you playing ball, got you working out.

11:37.432 --> 11:41.467
It's like a street camp.
You get some hookups going.

11:41.502 --> 11:42.969
Yeah?

11:43.004 --> 11:44.914
Yeah.

11:44.939 --> 11:47.063
If it gets tight on the inside,

11:47.088 --> 11:48.898
tight when you get back on the outside.

11:48.923 --> 11:51.190
Get some eses looking out for you.

11:51.225 --> 11:53.158
Not a bitch no more.

11:53.194 --> 11:56.228
I'm not a bitch.

11:56.263 --> 11:57.696
Yeah, say that for real.

11:57.732 --> 11:58.831
I'm not a bitch!

11:58.866 --> 12:00.899
Hey! Watch your language.

12:00.935 --> 12:04.002
Next time you get sat up in
front of your parole officer,

12:04.038 --> 12:06.305
just be like, "yes, sir, no, sir."

12:06.340 --> 12:07.340
Give them your grill,

12:07.375 --> 12:09.274
and they'll slide you right out of here.

12:09.310 --> 12:11.410
Right?

12:11.445 --> 12:14.012
Juvie ain't nothing.

12:14.048 --> 12:17.495
Hang close, do how I do,

12:17.520 --> 12:19.086
and you'll be out of here in no time.

12:25.076 --> 12:27.497
I didn't know you were
coming in last night.

12:27.522 --> 12:29.568
Why didn't you tell me? I-I
could have picked you up.

12:29.593 --> 12:31.889
No, it was just easier this way. I
didn't want you and mom to get in...

12:31.924 --> 12:33.844
Huh. Yeah, I mean, you
go out to dinner with her?

12:33.860 --> 12:35.926
- Are you staying with her?
- Russ, come on. I don't want to get into that.

12:35.962 --> 12:38.062
No, of course. Of... of course.

12:38.097 --> 12:40.664
Well, how... how you doing? You look good.

12:40.700 --> 12:43.434
- You're... army still good for you?
- Yeah.

12:43.469 --> 12:44.869
- Yeah, I like Germany.
- Yeah?

12:44.904 --> 12:48.806
- Um, I get to see a bit of Europe on my time off.
- Yeah.

12:48.841 --> 12:52.343
- You doing all right?
- Yeah, yeah. I'm... I'm okay.

12:52.378 --> 12:53.978
Feels good to be busy.

12:54.013 --> 12:56.080
Yeah.

12:56.115 --> 12:59.483
You, uh... you still, um, staying at the...

12:59.519 --> 13:01.285
I-I got a, um...

13:01.320 --> 13:03.220
A motel... room. Yeah.

13:03.256 --> 13:05.990
I'm looking for something more like a...

13:06.025 --> 13:07.625
Like a home, you know?

13:07.660 --> 13:10.394
A sublet or, you know, a place...

13:10.429 --> 13:12.363
A place that has a living
room and a... and a fridge

13:12.398 --> 13:14.531
that I don't have to crouch down to reach.

13:14.557 --> 13:16.156
So you plan on staying here a while?

13:16.191 --> 13:18.555
Yeah, well, at least through the trial.

13:18.580 --> 13:20.666
People here are nice.

13:20.691 --> 13:26.502
Yeah. You seem to be going
to a lot of effort here. Hmm?

13:26.527 --> 13:30.089
Getting a new job, leaving Arizona.

13:30.125 --> 13:32.559
No, I'm gonna... I'm
gonna keep my place there.

13:32.594 --> 13:35.628
I mean, I... I plan to go back eventually.

13:35.664 --> 13:36.944
So why is it so important to you

13:36.965 --> 13:39.132
that Matt gets buried in Oakland?

13:39.167 --> 13:42.068
Come on. Couldn't you
just let this one play out?

13:42.103 --> 13:43.703
Matt and Gwen should be buried together.

13:43.738 --> 13:45.672
Well, I spoke to Eve,

13:45.707 --> 13:47.106
and she says that Gwen's getting better.

13:47.142 --> 13:48.575
She might make it.

13:48.610 --> 13:50.176
And if she does get better,

13:50.212 --> 13:53.479
then Gwen gets to decide
what happens to Matt's body,

13:53.515 --> 13:55.748
so  it's just a...

13:55.784 --> 13:58.017
It's a whole lot of hurt over nothing.

13:59.855 --> 14:01.921
Not for nothing.

14:04.759 --> 14:07.794
I'm not afraid of your mother anymore.

14:07.829 --> 14:09.095
And she knows it.

14:09.130 --> 14:11.731
You know, Russ...

14:11.766 --> 14:14.300
It's really hard for
me to come all this way

14:14.336 --> 14:15.602
with everything that's going on

14:15.637 --> 14:17.070
and have the two of you
still go at it like this.

14:17.105 --> 14:18.872
You're right. You're right. You're right.

14:18.907 --> 14:22.308
You're right. I'm, uh...

14:22.344 --> 14:25.111
Listen, I-I'm sorry if I...

14:25.146 --> 14:27.849
I don't... I don't want you... I don't

14:27.874 --> 14:30.325
- want you to be in the middle, okay?
- Well, it's not...

14:30.351 --> 14:31.950
- Russ.
- Yeah?

14:31.985 --> 14:33.118
You with a customer?

14:33.152 --> 14:35.519
Yeah, I'm, uh... I'm on.

14:35.556 --> 14:36.822
Okay. Excuse me, sir.

14:36.857 --> 14:38.323
Oh. Yeah.

14:47.334 --> 14:49.539
The case had not finished
a technical review.

14:49.564 --> 14:52.637
We only had the preliminary
findings of one criminalist.

14:52.673 --> 14:55.273
- What you did was illegal and immoral.
- We were waiting to hear from another...

14:55.308 --> 14:57.875
No, I'm afraid it's not.
It's called being thorough.

14:57.911 --> 15:00.011
Don't you condescend to me.

15:00.046 --> 15:02.947
I'm an educated woman.
don't treat me like I'm not.

15:02.983 --> 15:04.750
I'm sure.

15:04.785 --> 15:06.718
But we're talking about the law.

15:06.754 --> 15:08.887
So, if there are other legal issues

15:08.922 --> 15:10.222
you're having trouble with,

15:10.257 --> 15:12.524
I encourage you to
reach out to this office,

15:12.559 --> 15:15.360
and we'll try to explain them

15:15.396 --> 15:18.697
in a way that you're more fully understand.

15:18.732 --> 15:20.699
"Soderbergh."

15:20.733 --> 15:23.367
What kind of name is that?

15:25.472 --> 15:27.939
My brother deserves due process.

15:27.975 --> 15:29.441
We're taking this to a judge,

15:29.476 --> 15:32.644
and we're getting a bail hearing.

15:36.282 --> 15:39.139
It's the best rehab facility
in Stanislaus County.

15:39.164 --> 15:41.280
- It's Stanislaus, like "coleslaw."
- I had a nice, long talk with a

15:41.305 --> 15:44.546
woman who runs it, and she said that
even though there's a waiting list,

15:44.571 --> 15:47.422
- they would take you next Tuesday.
- I'm not going.

15:47.447 --> 15:50.257
I don't have to, as long as I keep
going to the meetings, right, dad?

15:50.282 --> 15:51.848
Did I say that? I didn't say that.

15:51.884 --> 15:55.252
The meetings are good, but
they're not good enough.

15:55.287 --> 15:59.212
You need something more... comprehensive.

16:01.894 --> 16:04.127
Your father and Brian and I

16:04.163 --> 16:06.396
- all want the same thing... Aubry?
- Yeah?

16:06.432 --> 16:08.031
And what's that?

16:08.067 --> 16:10.133
For you to get back on your feet.

16:10.169 --> 16:12.305
To get clean.

16:13.275 --> 16:14.541
Do you remember that card store they opened

16:14.577 --> 16:16.009
last year on Kilbourn Avenue?

16:16.045 --> 16:17.911
No, and I haven't been to
Milwaukee in how long now?

