28:01.064 --> 28:03.665
and I'm not about to sit
around and fight with you all

28:03.700 --> 28:05.833
while the animal who shot him walks.

28:05.869 --> 28:07.502
I mean, what is the...

28:07.537 --> 28:10.872
"An eye for an eye," isn't that right, Eve?

28:21.878 --> 28:23.978
It's a glorious day, isn't it?

28:24.013 --> 28:25.013
Yes.

28:25.014 --> 28:27.148
Yes, it is glorious.

28:27.183 --> 28:28.816
You know, I remember there was a time

28:28.852 --> 28:30.685
when I would say, "it's a nice day.

28:30.720 --> 28:33.754
The sky is blue, but I
wish it was even bluer."

28:35.158 --> 28:38.993
"The temperature's right, but I
wish it were more to my liking."

28:39.028 --> 28:43.478
Does that sound familiar?

28:43.503 --> 28:46.736
I worked hard. I was
blessed with good things.

28:46.761 --> 28:50.972
I had a house full... a house
full of things, just things.

28:51.007 --> 28:56.068
But for all I had, I still wanted more.

28:56.093 --> 28:59.226
So I bought a bigger house.

29:00.842 --> 29:02.786
And I filled that house with things.

29:06.819 --> 29:08.225
But I stayed empty.

29:10.007 --> 29:11.359
I was empty.

29:13.054 --> 29:15.631
And I put that emptiness on my family.

29:17.902 --> 29:21.437
If you can't even understand
the value of things,

29:21.472 --> 29:24.006
then how can you understand
the value of people?

29:25.677 --> 29:28.377
I couldn't help myself.
I was a slave to wanting.

29:28.413 --> 29:30.479
I mean, that's the truth.

29:30.515 --> 29:33.716
Debt is slavery. Credit is slavery.

29:33.751 --> 29:35.351
Preach!

29:35.386 --> 29:39.355
That's their way... to
be greedy and selfish.

29:40.169 --> 29:42.403
That's how they live.

29:42.438 --> 29:44.505
That's what they teach their children.

29:44.540 --> 29:47.274
"Buy this, buy that, have this, have that."

29:47.310 --> 29:48.642
Yeah.

29:48.678 --> 29:53.514
But when you live like that,
when you live like they live,

29:53.549 --> 29:56.250
that's when you can feel it in your heart.

29:56.285 --> 29:59.153
