or a skirt and a blouse

30:57.688 --> 31:00.389
with classic lines and your true colors.

31:00.424 --> 31:02.358
Don't wear a suit. It's too severe.

31:02.393 --> 31:05.594
You're there as a mother.

31:05.630 --> 31:07.363
It makes a difference.

31:07.398 --> 31:09.465
Did it for you?

31:13.270 --> 31:17.606
My daughter's killer was a monster,

31:17.642 --> 31:19.241
someone who had been
violent his whole life,

31:19.276 --> 31:21.644
never had a job, never finished school.

31:21.679 --> 31:23.746
On the first day of his trial,

31:23.781 --> 31:26.181
he showed up wearing glasses,

31:27.380 --> 31:28.979
and he didn't even know how to read.

31:29.015 --> 31:31.715
Was he black? No, he was white.

31:31.751 --> 31:33.017
He wore a suit and tie.

31:33.052 --> 31:35.786
He... he looked like a college student.

31:35.822 --> 31:37.555
And his lawyer told all these stories,

31:37.590 --> 31:39.190
all these sad, sad stories

31:39.225 --> 31:41.125
about how he'd been abused as a child.

31:41.160 --> 31:45.162
He'd never had a chance at a real...

31:45.187 --> 31:48.074
I went out and bought... a blue dress

31:48.099 --> 31:49.532
that I thought would make me feel

31:49.567 --> 31:51.968
the opposite of what I was feeling...

31:52.003 --> 31:56.806
Confident... because I wanted
to be strong for my daughter.

31:56.841 --> 32:01.511
But the defense painted
this picture of me...

32:01.546 --> 32:04.747
As this... cold woman.

32:04.783 --> 32:06.849
That's... anyone can see that's...

32:06.885 --> 32:10.419
I know. I know. I'm not
saying it to make you...

32:10.455 --> 32:15.811
The defense made it
sound like it was my fault

32:15.836 --> 32:17.994
that my daughter had been killed.

32:18.029 --> 32:19.936
And the jury looked at her killer

32:19.961 --> 32:23.199
in his suit and glasses
and felt sorry for him.

32:24.009 --> 32:25.442
And the press kept writing

32:25.477 --> 32:29.947
about this cold woman in her blue dress.

32:32.618 --> 32:35.786
So I lost that battle.

32:35.821 --> 32:39.056
All I can do is pass on
to you what I've learned.

32:39.091 --> 32:41.992
These things do matter.

33:14.180 --> 33:16.748
When Carter Nix was first arraigned,

33:16.783 --> 33:19.650
he was remanded based
on the alleged strength

33:19.686 --> 33:22.720
of the people's case, and
now we see that their case

33:22.756 --> 33:25.089
is not nearly as strong as they portrayed.

33:25.125 --> 33:28.960
In fact, since this court
denied my client bail,

33:28.995 --> 33:31.419
we have found out a few things.

33:31.444 --> 33:35.299
The gun found on my client
was not the murder weapon.

33:35.335 --> 33:37.235
The semen found on Mrs. Skokie

33:37.270 --> 33:40.505
does not match the semen of my client.

33:40.540 --> 33:44.242
The truth is... Mrs.
Skokie wasn't raped at all,

33:44.277 --> 33:48.464
but had consensual sex with
men other than her husband.

33:48.489 --> 33:50.753
Another change in circumstances

33:50.778 --> 33:53.933
was the discovery of a
sellable amount of drugs

33:53.958 --> 33:56.069
found in Mr. and Mrs. Skokie's home.

33:56.104 --> 33:57.770
"Sellable" is a reach, Your Honor.

33:57.806 --> 34:00.840
What would you call it,
then? A lifetime supply?

34:00.876 --> 34:04.852
Mr. Skokie had no record of
drug dealing or anything else.

34:04.877 --> 34:06.892
There were strangers in
the house, Your Honor.

34:06.917 --> 34:09.166
Mr. and Mrs. Skokie's activities

34:09.190 --> 34:11.114
brought a criminal element into their home.

34:11.150 --> 34:13.344
That's speculation at its worst, counselor.

34:13.369 --> 34:15.203
You have no proof, no police
reports, no witness testimony.

34:15.239 --> 34:18.974
I ask for a complete dismissal
of all charges, Your Honor.

34:19.009 --> 34:20.275
Your Honor, we have a witness

34:20.311 --> 34:22.377
that puts the defendant
at the scene of the crime.

34:22.413 --> 34:26.114
After which, he returns with
the murder victim's wallet.

34:26.150 --> 34:29.184
Well, I'm not going to dismiss the charges.

34:29.219 --> 34:30.552
The people's case remains compelling

34:30.588 --> 34:33.621
and deserves to move forward
to preliminary examination.

34:33.657 --> 34:37.826
However, the proof of Mr.
Nix's guilt is not as evident

34:37.860 --> 34:40.762
as when the court determined
bail was not appropriate.

34:40.797 --> 34:43.831
Therefore, I am setting bail at $1 million

34:43.867 --> 34:46.156
with a fully collateralized bond,

34:46.181 --> 34:49.043
plus pre-trial monitoring by
the department of probations,

34:49.068 --> 34:51.696
including but not limited
to ankle monitoring.

35:09.126 --> 35:11.393
When, uh, Brother Timothy
said "lifetime supply,"

35:11.427 --> 35:13.527
oh, my...

35:13.563 --> 35:17.298
Look at them... with their
head scarves... celebrating.

35:20.930 --> 35:22.546
You people have no right

35:22.571 --> 35:24.312
talking about my son like that.

35:24.337 --> 35:25.953
He was a good man, and you
can all just go to hell!

35:25.978 --> 35:26.978
Mom!

35:29.848 --> 35:32.916
I made it worse...

35:32.930 --> 35:34.730
- It's all right.
- They're not gonna write about that?

35:34.766 --> 35:36.899
They're not gonna write about
me yelling and being hysterical,

35:36.934 --> 35:39.568
all of them standing there,
laughing and grinning?

35:40.425 --> 35:42.323
You said what you felt.

35:42.348 --> 35:44.948
That isn't me. I don't lose myself.

35:44.973 --> 35:47.862
I'm controlled. I can control...

35:51.102 --> 35:54.237
Would you... would you
take him away from here?

35:54.272 --> 35:56.906
Yeah, of course. I don't
want to walk out with him.

36:08.475 --> 36:11.384
You're working so hard, sweetheart.

36:11.409 --> 36:13.643
Daddy and I are proud of you.

36:13.678 --> 36:16.122
We're here for you.

36:16.147 --> 36:18.341
We'll always be here for you.

36:18.366 --> 36:19.799
She didn't love us.

36:19.834 --> 36:21.567
- She humored us.
- Don't.

36:21.603 --> 36:22.869
She tolerated us.

36:22.904 --> 36:25.271
Stop feeling sorry for yourself.

36:25.306 --> 36:27.373
This isn't about you.

36:27.409 --> 36:29.442
That is not the girl we raised.

36:29.477 --> 36:32.761
She is our child. She
will always be our child.

36:32.786 --> 36:37.088
And I won't abandon her now
when she needs us the most.

36:38.734 --> 36:40.748
What has happened to you?

36:42.180 --> 36:44.090
I read the police file.

36:46.548 --> 36:49.852
The men whose semen was found inside her...

36:49.887 --> 36:51.453
The police talked to them... you did that?!

36:51.489 --> 36:53.088
And they went into great
detail about what...

36:53.124 --> 36:55.191
How could you invade her
privacy?! How could you do that?!

36:55.226 --> 36:56.881
Because one of us has to be realistic.

36:56.906 --> 36:58.835
You are not being realistic.

36:58.860 --> 37:02.809
Gwen is not normal... not sexually, no.

37:02.834 --> 37:04.767
- It doesn't matter!
- She has problems.

37:04.802 --> 37:07.536
My god, yes, I know she has problems.

37:07.572 --> 37:08.871
I know she needs help,

37:08.906 --> 37:10.973
but I'm not gonna sit here
and argue about her sex life

37:11.008 --> 37:12.368
when, my god, we don't even know...

37:12.376 --> 37:14.443
What's going on here?
Were you guys touching her?

37:14.478 --> 37:15.911
What? No.

37:15.947 --> 37:17.546
No. What's the matter?

37:17.582 --> 37:19.148
Her heart rate started racing.

37:19.183 --> 37:21.584
- Is she all right?
- What... what does that mean?

37:21.619 --> 37:24.934
Page Dr... Page Dr. Parks to room 203.

37:24.959 --> 37:26.725
What... what's wrong?

37:26.761 --> 37:28.326
Uh, the doctor might want
to give her a sedative.

37:28.351 --> 37:30.185
Sedative? She's in a coma.

37:30.210 --> 37:33.031
Yeah, well, if she wasn't
responding to physical stimuli,

37:33.067 --> 37:35.167
then she was responding to
something you were saying.

37:35.202 --> 37:37.436
She's waking up.

38:09.170 --> 38:11.403
No! No! No!

38:14.608 --> 38:16.041
No.

38:16.076 --> 38:20.535
Guard! Aah! Guard!

38:20.560 --> 38:22.794
No! Guard!

38:22.829 --> 38:25.196
Guard! Help!

38:25.231 --> 38:26.998
What do you mean, you'll
get the bail money?

38:27.033 --> 38:29.100
By the mercy of Allah.

38:29.135 --> 38:31.468
A $100,000 bond?

38:31.493 --> 38:33.110
Where are you gonna get
that kind of cash from?

38:33.135 --> 38:35.495
- I have it.
- How?

38:35.530 --> 38:38.565
I had some in savings,
and then I took out a loan.

38:38.600 --> 38:41.334
And for the rest, I took
a collection at the temple.

38:41.369 --> 38:44.704
The people came together, and
they gave from their hearts.

38:44.739 --> 38:47.073
Them people don't know me.

38:47.108 --> 38:50.143
If you're known by Allah,
then you're known by us.

38:50.178 --> 38:52.445
Your freedom is so close.

38:52.480 --> 38:55.682
So pay the money. Get
me the hell out of here.

38:55.717 --> 38:58.108
If you're willing to accept our freedom,

38:58.133 --> 39:00.273
then you have to be willing
to accept what comes with it.

39:00.298 --> 39:02.732
I told you before... I'm
not begging you for anything.

39:02.767 --> 39:05.167
What's happening here is bigger than you.

39:05.203 --> 39:08.437
This is about every black
man who cannot get justice.

39:08.473 --> 39:10.548
You need to represent.

39:10.573 --> 39:14.002
You need to be the voice for
people who do not have a voice.

39:17.312 --> 39:19.955
And you need to stay away from that girl.

39:21.483 --> 39:24.218
Look, Aubry... she's not
what you're saying she is.

39:24.253 --> 39:25.852
She's bad for you.

39:25.888 --> 39:28.121
And unless you're able to admit
it and turn away from her...

39:28.157 --> 39:31.091
- Look, you don't understand.
- I have been there, Carter.

39:32.133 --> 39:33.583
I failed myself.

39:33.608 --> 39:35.060
I failed other people.

39:35.085 --> 39:37.193
I love her.

39:40.180 --> 39:42.443
You can hate whitey all you want.

39:43.078 --> 39:45.645
Aubry... I love her.

39:48.450 --> 39:50.820
This is not a negotiation.

39:50.845 --> 39:53.608
It's a condition.

39:53.633 --> 39:56.679
I understand more than you think.

39:57.692 --> 40:01.427
And once you've elevated
yourself, you'll thank me.

40:13.456 --> 40:18.278
I don't think you can
imagine how unhappy Gwen was,

40:20.281 --> 40:22.815
how she... she was driven
to do things with men.

40:25.351 --> 40:28.061
Well, she was in a bad situation.

40:28.086 --> 40:30.281
Yeah, but when?

40:31.008 --> 40:32.892
When was it bad? When
she was with your brother?

40:34.153 --> 40:36.120
Or when she was with us?

40:37.998 --> 40:42.393
This, um... this story that my mom tells

40:42.428 --> 40:47.798
about my brother signing up
after 9/11, being a hero...

40:47.834 --> 40:50.768
It's not true.

40:50.803 --> 40:53.037
Matt was doing drugs and selling drugs

40:53.072 --> 40:55.473
even back then.

40:55.508 --> 40:57.108
And mom didn't know what to do with him,

40:57.143 --> 41:00.711
so... she made him enlist.

41:00.747 --> 41:03.481
She was the one that put him in the army.

41:03.516 --> 41:05.917
- He didn't want to go.
- Why are you telling me this?

41:05.952 --> 41:07.885
Because you need to know.

41:07.921 --> 41:11.155
These lies... it's... it's all my mom has.

41:12.225 --> 41:16.552
Her husband split on her. Her son's dead.

41:18.718 --> 41:20.960
All she has left is a fantasy.

41:20.999 --> 41:22.766
You want me to feel sorry for her?

41:22.801 --> 41:25.368
I want you to look at my family

41:25.404 --> 41:28.071
and see us for the freak show that we are.

41:31.043 --> 41:34.077
And I want you to do better than us.

41:34.112 --> 41:36.546
I should never have looked at those files.

41:36.581 --> 41:38.848
No. I had no business reading...

41:38.884 --> 41:40.183
The only thing that matters

41:40.218 --> 41:44.621
is that Gwen has a real shot at surviving.

41:46.058 --> 41:47.390
So if it's all right, um,

41:47.426 --> 41:49.793
I want to stick around and...

41:53.065 --> 41:58.034
Try and see if I can be of use somehow.

41:58.070 --> 42:00.036
My family's busted up.

42:00.072 --> 42:03.707
It's never gonna get fixed.

42:03.742 --> 42:06.309
But you... Gwen, and Eve...

